note.text:
Drugs of Abuse Note:
- These screening cutoffs are for medical/treatment/clinical purposes only.
- For all non-medical purposes, samples should be referred for confirmatory testing
- The concentration value must be greater than or equal to the cutoff to be reported as positive, and less than the cutoff to be reported as negative.
- Follow-up confirmation testing by mass spectrometry is recommended for unexpected results.
- Interpretive questions should be directed to the laboratory.
- This test was performed in a CLIA certified laboratory.

Analyte                            Cutoff (ng/mL) 
Amphetamine                        1000 
Barbiturate                        200 
Benzodiazepine                     200 
Cannabinoids                       50 
Cocaine                            300 
Methadone/Methadone Metabolite*    100 
Opiates                            300 
Oxycodone                          100 
Phencyclidine (PCP)                25

* At BH-MC, GH, and LMH the screening cutoff for Methadone is 300 ng/mL.
